<item>
            <title>[FLINK-6183] TaskMetricGroup may not be cleanup when Task.run() is never called or exits early</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-6183</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The TaskMetricGroup is created when a Task is created. It is cleaned up at the end of Task.run() in the finally block. If however run() is never called due some failure between the creation and the call to run the metric group is never closed. This also means that the JobMetricGroup is never closed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13058953">FLINK-6183</key>
            <summary>TaskMetricGroup may not be cleanup when Task.run() is never called or exits early</summary>
